  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Microwave ablation (MWA) is the most recent development in the field of local ablative
      therapies. The aim of this study was to evaluate the variability and reproducibility of
      single-probe MWA versus radiofrequency ablation (RFA) of metastatic liver tumours smaller
      than 3 cm in patients without underlying liver disease.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
